# 05 — Component Selection

## Rule

**No BOM entry without qualification** (or explicit provisional authorization in the task).

## Never infer continuous current from

Part number · marketing text · headline current limit · abs max rating · package size

## Qualification workflow

```
Requirements → Candidates → Datasheet → Electrical → Thermal → Availability → Lifecycle → Decision
```

## Required evidence (TBD until recorded)

- Exact MPN, datasheet revision and URL
- Lifecycle and automotive qualification status
- Continuous vs pulse vs limit current (distinct)
- Thermal: Rds, Rth, cooling, simultaneous operation
- Alternatives and procurement risk

## Channel classes

Use abstract class (HS05, HS15, HS30, HS60) until qualified for defined conditions (voltage, T_amb, PCB, duty).

Do not add components in WP/documentation tasks unless task authorizes it.

Report path: `hardware/qualification/{category}/{manufacturer}_{mpn}_qualification.md`

Approved BOM reference (when qualified): `docs/007` — status per document, not frozen by this rule pack.
